# post-research skill — credential template
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .vibe/skills/post-research/.env.example .vibe/skills/post-research/.env
#
# BOTH platforms are OPTIONAL. The skill works without any credentials but
# falls back to proxy tiers (Jina Reader, twitter-thread.com, etc.) which
# may fail for login-walled content.
#
# For extraction instructions, see:
#   references/bird-setup.md    (Twitter/X)
#   references/redbook-setup.md (Red Note)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Twitter / X   (https://x.com)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# auth_token  — your session token, ~40-char hex string
# ct0         — CSRF token, ~160-char alphanumeric string
# Both found at: DevTools → Application → Cookies → https://x.com
#
TWITTER_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWITTER_CT0=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Red Note / Xiaohongshu   (https://www.xiaohongshu.com)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# a1          — device/session identifier, long alphanumeric string
# web_session — session token, starts with "040062"... or similar
# Both found at: DevTools → Application → Cookies → https://www.xiaohongshu.com
#
XHS_A1=
XHS_WEB_SESSION=
